<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate.ejs") %>

<style>
  :root {
    --primary-color: #3498db;
    --text-color: #2c3e50;
    --light-bg: #ecf0f1;
  }

  .banner {
    background: url("assets/about-banner.jpg") center/cover no-repeat;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3.125rem 1.25rem;
    color: black;
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-top: 4rem;
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 56.25rem;
    margin: auto;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  h2 {
    color: var(--text-color);
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.9375rem;
  }

  .faq h3 {
    background: var(--primary-color);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.625rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-top: 0.625rem;
    border-radius: 0.3125rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: background 0.3s;
  }

  .faq h3::after {
    content: "\25BC";
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .faq h3.active::after {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .faq p {
    display: none;
    padding: 0.625rem;
    background: var(--light-bg);
    border-left: 0.3125rem solid var(--primary-color);
    width: 96%;
  }
</style>

<div class="banner">
  <h1>About HopeHands</h1>
  <p>
    Empowering skilled yet illiterate individuals in Nagpur by connecting them
    with meaningful employment.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="content-wrapper">
  <h2>Our Mission</h2>
  <p>
    HopeHands is dedicated to helping skilled workers in Nagpur find stable job
    opportunities. Whether you are a carpenter, cleaner, or mechanic, our
    platform ensures that your skills are recognized and rewarded.
  </p>
  <p>
    We aim to bridge the gap between skilled laborers and businesses that
    require their expertise. By providing a seamless platform for hiring, we
    ensure that both workers and employers benefit from a transparent and
    efficient system.
  </p>
  <br /><br />

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq1', this)">Who can register on HopeHands?</h3>
    <p id="faq1">
      Any skilled worker residing in Nagpur who needs employment can register on
      our platform. We welcome individuals who have expertise in fields such as
      carpentry, plumbing, cleaning, mechanics, and other hands-on trades. Our
      goal is to provide equal job opportunities for everyone, ensuring they get
      fair wages and a stable livelihood. By registering, workers can showcase
      their skills and connect with potential employers looking for trustworthy
      professionals.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq2', this)">How do employers find workers?</h3>
    <p id="faq2">
      Employers can browse profiles and connect directly with skilled workers
      based on their needs. Our platform provides a search and filter system to
      help businesses quickly identify workers with the right expertise. Once a
      match is found, they can contact the worker and finalize hiring
      arrangements seamlessly. Additionally, we ensure that employer reviews and
      worker ratings help maintain a reliable hiring process for both parties.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq3', this)">Is HopeHands free to use?</h3>
    <p id="faq3">
      Yes, registration for workers is completely free, ensuring equal
      opportunities for everyone. We believe that financial constraints should
      not be a barrier to employment. Employers, however, may have access to
      premium features for additional benefits, such as priority listing and
      advanced filtering, which help in finding the best workers quickly and
      efficiently.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq4', this)">
      What types of jobs are available?
    </h3>
    <p id="faq4">
      HopeHands connects workers with jobs in carpentry, cleaning, mechanics,
      plumbing, and many more skilled trades. We continuously expand our job
      categories to include various skilled professions, allowing more workers
      to find suitable employment. Whether it's daily wage work or full-time
      employment, we aim to cater to diverse job preferences.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq5', this)">
      How does HopeHands verify worker skills?
    </h3>
    <p id="faq5">
      We conduct basic skill assessments and rely on employer feedback to verify
      the expertise of registered workers. We also encourage workers to upload
      proof of prior work experience or certifications to enhance their
      profiles. Additionally, workers with positive employer reviews gain better
      visibility on the platform, helping them secure more job opportunities.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq6', this)">How can I contact support?</h3>
    <p id="faq6">
      You can reach out to our support team via email or phone. Our dedicated
      team is available to assist with any issues related to registration, job
      postings, or hiring processes. We also have a help center with FAQs and
      troubleshooting guides for common issues.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq7', this)">
      Can workers choose their job preferences?
    </h3>
    <p id="faq7">
      Yes, workers can specify their job preferences, availability, and location
      preferences to ensure they are matched with the most suitable employers.
      They can also update their profiles anytime to reflect new skills or
      experiences, helping them increase their chances of being hired.
    </p>

    <h3 onclick="toggleAnswer('faq8', this)">
      Are there any training programs available?
    </h3>
    <p id="faq8">
      HopeHands is working on introducing training programs to help workers
      enhance their skills and improve employability. These programs will focus
      on industry-specific skills, customer service, and safety training to
      ensure workers are well-prepared for their roles.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  function toggleAnswer(id, element) {
    var answer = document.getElementById(id);
    if (answer.style.display === "block") {
      answer.style.display = "none";
      element.classList.remove("active");
    } else {
      answer.style.display = "block";
      element.classList.add("active");
    }
  }
</script>
